    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-29T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="340"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/4–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-29T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 29, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 30—1:46 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 301. When Sun Fo received me today in his heavily guarded Tungshan
                    residence, he obviously had jitters and was most uncommunicative. <pb
                        facs="0297" n="287" xml:id="pg_287"/> He confirmed, however, Gimo’s proposal
                    at Hangchow to Li Tsung-jen for creation supreme policy committee which Gimo
                    would head and which would be superior to Cabinet. Sun tried to leave me with
                    impression Li had agreed and insisted creation some such organ capable quick
                    action was needed. Its creation would not affect Legislative and Control Yuans,
                    he said. He was obviously depressed as well as jittery and insisted without
                    conviction that Shanghai would be defended.</p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 301, repeated Nanking 236, Shanghai 189.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
